<h2>Navigation Bar</h2>

<p>This library includes a module for a navigation bar user interface element:</p>

<ul class="modules">
    <li><%= DOC.modules.render('Entity/Nav/Bar') %></li>
</ul>

<div class="examples">

    <h3>Basic Usage</h3>

    <p>The minimal definition is simply a <code>nav.bar</code> containing a <code>ul</code> or <code>ol</code>.</p>

    <pre class="prettyprint">&lt;nav class="bar"&gt;
    &lt;ul&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a&gt;Item 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;!-- more list items... --&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/nav&gt;</pre>
    
    <p>The nav bar renders as a full-width bar within its container. So long as the elements haven't overflowed, they will be listed from left to right across the bar.</p>

    <nav class="bar">
        <ul>
            <li><a>Item 1</a></li>
            <li><a>Item 2</a></li>
            <li><a>Item 3</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>
    
    <p>If they have overflowed, meanwhile, they will vanish and an icon will appear that causes the menu to drop down when pressed:</p>

    <nav class="bar">
        <ul>
            <li><a>Item 1</a></li>
            <li><a>Item 2</a></li>
            <li><a>Item 3</a></li>
            <li><a>Item 4</a></li>
            <li><a>Item 5</a></li>
            <li><a>Item 6</a></li>
            <li><a>Item 7</a></li>
            <li><a>Item 8</a></li>
            <li><a>Item 9</a></li>
            <li><a>Item 10</a></li>
            <li><a>Item 11</a></li>
            <li><a>Item 12</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>
    
    <p>A header element (<code>h1</code>-<code>h6</code>) may be added as the <em>first</em> child of <code>nav.bar</code> to display a title for the bar:</p>
    
    <pre class="prettyprint">&lt;nav class="bar"&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;Title&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;ul&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a&gt;Item 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;!-- more list items... --&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/nav&gt;</pre>

    <nav class="bar">
        <h1>Title</h1>
        <ul>
            <li><a>Item 1</a></li>
            <li><a>Item 2</a></li>
            <li><a>Item 3</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>
    
    <p>The header should always be the first child of <code>nav.bar</code>, but the <code>.float-right</code> class may be applied to it to position it on the right side of the bar.</p>
    
    <pre class="prettyprint">&lt;nav class="bar"&gt;
